<title>UK: No rights issue, so Scotia shares rebound.</title>
<headline>No rights issue, so Scotia shares rebound.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Scotia Holdings Plc rebounded from their earlier losses on Tuesday after the British biotech company said it expected no rights issue until end-1997 or 1998 and announced a diabetic drug accord with Japan's Ajinomoto Co Inc.</p>
<p>The shares were 26p higher at 405 by 0933 GMT, having fallen to 365 earlier.</p>
